    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your r<strong>ed chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and strip your <strong>Thai basil leaves </strong>from their stalks, then add <strong>half</strong> your <strong>cashew nuts</strong> (you’ll use the rest later!) to a <strong>food processo</strong>r with the <strong>crushed garlic </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and blitz until smooth</p><p>Add the <strong>peeled ginger</strong>, <strong>chilli halves </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>chopped lemongrass</strong>, <strong>Thai basil stalks</strong>, <strong>dried lime leaf[ves]</strong> and <strong>fish sauce</strong> with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]<strong> </span>vegetable oil </strong>and a splash of <strong>cold water </strong>and blitz until a paste forms – this is your <strong>red Thai curry paste</strong></p>",
